D=ZRTGQMMYRQKGRPPZG93G |website=Amazon.com |accessdate= |date=May 5, 2015 |df= }}</ref><br />Seasons 1\u20135: September 1, 2015<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/offline.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150730014908/http://www.tvshowsondvd.com/news/Johnny-Test-Seasons-1-to-5/21366|url-status=dead|title=TVShowsOnDVD.com - Goodbye|archivedate=July 30, 2015|website=www.tvshowsondvd.com}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Critical===\n{{expand section|date=March 2013}}\nJoly Herman of [[Common Sense Media]] had written and posted a review of ''Johnny Test'' on [[Go.com]], at the time of the show's original debut on [[Kids' WB]]. In the review, Herman indicated that the series \"is an age-appropriate choice for kids\" and was \"surprisingly inventive and not as violent as other cartoons in this genre\", adding, \"The only thing worth mentioning: All the experiments Johnny undergoes are unattended by adults, which allows all types of zany plots to unfold.\" Herman gave the show three stars out of five.<ref>{{cite news|last=Herman|first=Joly|title=Television Review: Johnny Test - Kid-friendly 'toon is more imaginative than most.|url=http://family.go.com/entertainment/article-csm-81143-television-review--johnny-test-t/|work=[[Go.com]]|date=September 25, 2005|location=USA|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711102553/http://family.go.com/entertainment/article-csm-81143-television-review--johnny-test-t/|archivedate=2011-07-11|accessdate=2014-02-20}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\nIn 2006, the first season of the series was nominated for Outstanding Sound Editing - Live Action and Animation at the [[33rd Daytime Emmy Awards]] and a [[Golden Reel Award (Motion Picture Sound Editors)|Golden Reel Award]] for Best Sound Editing in Television Animation (for the episode pair, ''Deep Sea Johnny'' and ''Johnny and the Amazing Turbo Action Backpack'') at Motion Picture Sound Editors, USA. In 2007, the second season of the show won a [[Gemini Award]] for Best Direction in a Children's or Youth Program or Series (for the episode pair, ''Saturday Night's Alright for Johnny'' and ''Johnny's Mint Chip'')<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20071017.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202220142/http://thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20071017.php|url-status=dead|title=JOE SHERMAN WINS GEMINI FOR BEST DIRECTOR OF COOKIE JAR'S JOHNNY TEST|archivedate=December 2, 2010}}</ref> and in 2008, the third season was nominated for another Gemini Award, this time for Best Original Music Score for an Animated Program or Series (for the episode pair, ''Johnny vs. Bling-Bling 3'' and ''Stinkin' Johnny''); finally, in 2010, the show, in its fourth season, was nominated once more for yet another Gemini Award, this time wholly for Best Animated Program or Series (for the episode pair, ''Johnny Cakes'' and ''Johnny Tube'')<ref>{{cite news|url=http://anhkhoi.blogspot.com/2010/08/nominations-for-2010-gemini-awards.html|title=The Cultural Post: Nominations for the 2010 Gemini Awards|date=August 31, 2010|work=The Cultural Post|accessdate=2011-03-01}}</ref> and had been awarded a Grand Prize for Best Program - All Categories at [[Alliance for Children and Television|the Alliance for Children and Television]]'s 2009 Gala award ceremony, which ultimately marks the series' owner, [[Cookie Jar (company)|Cookie Jar]]'s first ACT award.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20090604.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202214033/http://thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20090604.php|url-status=dead|title=COOKIE JAR ENTERTAINMENT'S JOHNNY TEST WINS ALLIANCE FOR MEP GRAND PRIZE|archivedate=December 2, 2010}}</ref>\n\n==In other media==\n\n===Toys===\n[[Cookie Jar Entertainment|Cookie Jar]] had partnered with restaurant chain [[CKE Restaurants]] to offer a promotional ''Johnny Test'' toy campaign at its [[Carl's Jr.]] and [[Hardee's]] restaurants in the U.S. and Mexico, one of the four custom-designed [[Premium segment|premiums]] with the purchase of their Cool Kids Combo meals; The campaign ran from June 28, 2010, through until August 24, 2010, with Carl's Jr. also having subsequently presented a ''Johnny Test'' soccer-themed promotion in Mexico, which lasted June 7 \u2013 July 25, 2010, to coincide with the country's [[2010 FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] activities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.toonzone.net/news/articles/33935/johnny-test-kids-meals-at-carls-jr.-and-hardees|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614014508/http://www.toonzone.net/news/articles/33935/johnny-test-kids-meals-at-carls-jr.-and-hardees|url-status=dead|title=\"Johnny Test\" Kids Meals at Carl's Jr. and Hardee's - Animation News Discussion Cartoon Community|archivedate=June 14, 2011}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20101202145308/http://thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20100615.php COOKIE JAR ENTERTAINMENT PARTNERS WITH CARL'S JR. AND HARDEE'S RESTAURANTS FOR JOHNNY TEST PROMOTIONS IN U.S. AND MEXICO]</ref> Philippines-based fried chicken chain [[Jollibee]] advertised a similar toy campaign in their Kids' Meals as well, in the form of their ''Amazing Adventure Chasers'' mini-toyline.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://azraelsmerryland.blogspot.com/2010/06/toy-news-unleash-your-imagination-with.html|title=TOY NEWS : Unleash your imagination with Jollibee Kids Meal\u2019s new blockbuster toys : Johnny Test and Carp Captor Sakura}}</ref> In 2014, [[DHX Media]] signed a master toy license with Imports Dragon.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhxmedia.com/newsreleases/dhx-media-secures-electrifying-deal-with-imports-dragon-as-johnny-test-master-toy-partner/|title=DHX MEDIA SECURES ELECTRIFYING DEAL WITH IMPORTS DRAGON AS JOHNNY TEST MASTER TOY PARTNER|date=February 12, 2014|accessdate=January 4, 2018|publisher=[[DHX Media]]}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\n{{See also|Johnny Test (video game)}}\n\nOn January 21, 2010, another partnership had emerged between [[Cookie Jar (company)|Cookie Jar Entertainment]] and the mobile application developer Jirbo that resulted in two ''Johnny Test'' video games produced by the developer and made available exclusively for download from [[iTunes]], for free and for the [[iPhone]], [[iPod Touch]] and [[iPad]]. The first game, ''Johnny Test: Clone Zapper'', finds Johnny Test and Dukey engaged to combat an army of Johnny clones they accidentally created  from a clone machine, with the help of two special laser zapper guns as their only weapons to defeat the clones and destroy them personally, and the second game, ''Johnny Test: Bot Drop'', sees Johnny, Dukey and the Test twins going on a rescue chase, with Johnny and Dukey both piloting a bot drop plane to use the robot clones of Johnnies (first seen in ''[[List of Johnny Test episodes#101 Johnnies|101 Johnnies]]'') for the titular \"Bot Drops\" to eject them to safety in a moving rescue vehicle driven by Susan and Mary. In the plot of that latter aforementioned game, and like in each level of the game before it, Johnny has to aim and time to drop the robots so they will land safely onto the vehicle, then Johnny Test has saved the day once again. Both games are typical shoot-slinging and side-scrolling games that in all utilize the iPhone, iPod Touch and iPad's unique multi-touch capabilities and scrolling, and, as a whole, players of both games can compete on the worldwide high scores list of each level of the game and competitive players. Later in Spring of 2011, the series was finally officially licensed by [[Cookie Jar (company)|Cookie Jar]] for a new third, and fully console-handled video game, this time, however, to come out on [[Nintendo DS]]; a sneak preview and trailer of the game had been already included on the complete first and second seasons DVD set (as aforementioned above), and was released in March 29, 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20100120.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101202144757/http://thecookiejarcompany.com/press/cj_press_20100120.php|url-status=dead|title=COOKIE JAR ENTERTAINMENT AND JIRBO TEAM UP TO RELEASE NEW JOHNNY TEST GAMES FOR IPHONE AND IPOD TOUCH|archivedate=December 2, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kidscreen.com/2010/01/21/cookiejar-20100121/ |title= KidScreen - Cookie Jar gets in the game with Johnny Test |accessdate=2014-02-17}}</ref>\n\n===Comic books and graphic novels===\n[[Viper Comics]] announced in April 2011 that they would be publishing a Johnny Test [[graphic novel]] along with another Cookie Jar Group property, ''[[Inspector Gadget (franchise)|Inspector Gadget]]''.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://vipercomics.com/2011/04/13/fcbd-inspector-gadget-and-johnny-test/\n|title=Free Comic Book Day: Inspector Gadget and Johnny Test\n|publisher=Viper Comics\n|date=April 13, 2011\n}}</ref> The book was subsequently published with the title ''Johnny Test: The Once and Future Johnny''.<ref>\n{{cite book\n|title=Johnny Test: The Once and Future Johnny\n|first=Dale|last=Mettam\n|year=2011\n|publisher=Viper Comics\n|isbn=9780983367017\n}}</ref>\n\n===Amusement park===\nThe [[Granby Zoo]] in [[Granby, Quebec|Granby]], [[Quebec]] also has an [[amusement park]] called \"Parc Johnny Test Collection\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.zoodegranby.com/cgi-bin/zoo/search.html?fi=zones&st=db&sp=core_zones_main_rides&co=1&sf=z_code&se=00021&op=rm&nu=1&su=0&ml=1 | title=Zoo de Granby}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Animation|Cartoon|Television|Canada|United States}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150317143659/http://dhxmedia.com/shows/animation/johnnytest.html ''Johnny Test''] at [[DHX Media]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20070927005203/http://www.johnnytestanddukey.com/index.html ''Johnny Test'' official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120406173627/http://www.teletoon.com/teletoon3/teletoon.php?language=En&fun